<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1740,2017]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,242,1740,1765]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">MALE.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[393,481,1740,1765]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="7.6">7.6 mm</quantity>
, wing length 6.0 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,794,1740,1765]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Head</emphasis>
. Face strongly concave and moderately projected anteroventrally; frontal prominence weakly developed (similar to Fig. 
<number box="[866,878,1776,1800]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
J). Width of vertex at anterior ocellus a little more than 
<number box="[205,215,1812,1836]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[225,241,1812,1836]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="4.0">4</number>
of the width of head; depth of occipital fossa ca. 
<number box="[787,797,1812,1836]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[809,823,1812,1836]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="3.0">3</number>
of the width of eye in dorsal view. Width of face:width of head 
<number box="[246,257,1848,1872]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[261,306,1848,1872]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="3.9">3.9</number>
. Face black, medio-ventral part brownish, pale pollinose. Gena shiny black. Frons and vertex dull black; lunula shiny brown. Occiput dull black. Antenna brown, basoflagellomere darker dorsally; arista pilose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,246,1920,1945]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Thorax.</emphasis>
Colour blackish, weakly pollinose; postalar callus brownish; scutum semi-shiny, with a pair of indistinct darker submedial fascia; pile short, adpressed, reddish; scutellum short, about 
<number box="[1027,1062,1956,1981]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times broader than long, apically rounded; the pile similar to that on scutum; with a pair of long thin, dark, setae at apical margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1261,1333,1992,2017]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Wing,</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[1341,1409,1992,2017]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,248,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[225,1354,364,1512]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[222,1365,358,1516]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Wing. A. Sphegina (Sphegina) uncinata sp. n. (paratype). B. S. (Asiosphegina) furva sp. n. (paratype). C. S. (A.) nasuta sp. n. (paratype). D. S. (A.) crucivena sp. n. (paratype). E. S. (A.) crassispina sp. n. (paratype). F. S. (A.) bidens sp. n. (paratype). G. S. (A.) carinata sp. n. (paratype). H. S. (A.) index sp. n. (paratype). I. S. (A.) simplex sp. n. (paratype). Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288398/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[1394,1409,1992,2016]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
H.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,650]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Hyalinous, the infuscated pattern brownish, stigma yellowish. Cross vein dm-cu perpendicular to vein M 
<number box="[1405,1410,166,180]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1420,1429,166,180]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2.0">2</number>
, slightly s-curved; vein M 
<number box="[445,453,205,219]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1.0">1</number>
straight. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[565,628,190,215]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Legs.</emphasis>
Pro- and mesolegs yellow; tarsomeres 
<number box="[1093,1107,191,215]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="4.0">4</number>
and 
<number box="[1169,1183,190,215]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="5.0">5</number>
black. Metaleg: coxa brownish; trochanter yellow, simple; femur black, the narrower curved basal part yellow, antero-dorsally with 
<number box="[1422,1436,230,254]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2.0">2</number>
long dark erected setae near the apex (in 
<typeStatus box="[623,721,265,290]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
broken off, only 
<number box="[922,936,266,290]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2.0">2</number>
sockets visible); tibia without apico-ventral tooth, black, the basal 
<number box="[402,412,301,326]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[422,437,301,326]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="6.0">6</number>
and a broad annulus on the apical 
<number box="[825,835,302,326]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[846,861,302,326]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2.0">2</number>
yellow; tarsus blackish. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1138,1262,301,326]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Length ratio of tergites I, II, 
<date box="[301,435,337,362]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
III and IV 
<number box="[425,435,337,362]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
: 
<number box="[439,482,337,362]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="4.2">4.2</number>
: 
<number box="[486,527,337,362]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2.5">2.5</number>
: 
<number box="[532,570,337,362]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1.5">1.5</number>
; tergites shiny black, tergite III yellow on anterior 
<number box="[1154,1165,338,362]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1177,1192,338,362]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="3.0">3</number>
; pile of tergites short and adpressed, reddish and blackish; tergite I with 
<number box="[736,750,374,398]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="3.0">3</number>
black, widely separated setae at lateral margin (in 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,373,398]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
only 
<number box="[208,222,410,434]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2.0">2</number>
visible); sternite IV (
<figureCitation box="[464,535,409,434]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1899,1921]" captionTargetBox="[196,1377,716,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[196,1390,702,1877]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) index sp. n. (holotype). A. Posterior part of abdomen, lateral view; the unmodified pilosity omitted. B. Posterior part of sternite IV, ventral view; the unmodified pilosity omitted. C. Genitalia, lateral view. D. Left surstylus, lateral view. E. Left superior lobe, lateral view. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288405/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Figs 
<number box="[521,535,410,434]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B) mainly brown, the pile adpressed and pale, the strong setae black; sternite VI (
<figureCitation box="[197,265,445,470]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1899,1921]" captionTargetBox="[196,1377,716,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[196,1390,702,1877]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) index sp. n. (holotype). A. Posterior part of abdomen, lateral view; the unmodified pilosity omitted. B. Posterior part of sternite IV, ventral view; the unmodified pilosity omitted. C. Genitalia, lateral view. D. Left surstylus, lateral view. E. Left superior lobe, lateral view. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288405/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[251,265,446,470]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
A) with a long, narrow, straight process on anterior part and a conical tubercle on posterior part, black, with long, pale pile; sternite VII simple, black, with long pale pile; sternite VIII simple, black, with pale pile on anterior part, shorter than that on sternite VII. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[679,796,517,542]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Genitalia,</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[804,875,517,542]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1899,1921]" captionTargetBox="[196,1377,716,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[196,1390,702,1877]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) index sp. n. (holotype). A. Posterior part of abdomen, lateral view; the unmodified pilosity omitted. B. Posterior part of sternite IV, ventral view; the unmodified pilosity omitted. C. Genitalia, lateral view. D. Left surstylus, lateral view. E. Left superior lobe, lateral view. Scale 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/288405/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Figs 
<number box="[861,875,518,542]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
C–E. Note the strongly asymmetrical surstyli and superior lobes and the basomedial lobe on the surstylus. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[784,911,553,578]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">FEMALE.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
