<subSubSection box="[199,1342,625,650]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,650]" box="[199,1342,625,650]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,625,650]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is Latin, 
<taxonomicName box="[557,618,625,649]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="index">
<emphasis box="[557,618,625,649]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">index</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, forefinger, referring to the finger-like lobe on the superior lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
