<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,151,176]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[339,511,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="index">
<emphasis box="[339,511,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Sphegina index</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[656,779,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[656,779,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">S. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Except for the characters mentioned in the key they differ as follows: 
<number box="[280,292,188,212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
) the two lateralmost of the enlarged setae on the left side of male sternite IV are ca. twice longer than the longest one of the more medial setae (in 
<taxonomicName box="[688,816,224,247]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[688,816,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">S. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ca. five times longer), 
<number box="[1097,1112,224,248]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
) male superior lobe has an inconspicuous lobe baso-dorsally (pointed finger-like lobe) and 
<number box="[886,900,260,284]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.0">3</number>
) male superior lobe with a large flip-like lobe ventrally, partly covering a recurrent finger like lobe (small flip-like lobe in more dorsal position, far from a ventral straight finger-like lobe). For further discussion, see under 
<taxonomicName box="[811,934,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[811,934,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">S. carinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
